        output='[{"url": "https://www.winsavvy.com/average-revenue-per-user-arpu-by-industry-and-model", "title": "Average Revenue Per User (ARPU) by Industry and Model", "content": "\\u2014 generate about $1,500/month per customer in ARPU. This includes access to email marketing, CRM, analytics, and sometimes content tools. Businesses rely on these platforms to grow. They drive leads, automate follow-ups, and keep deals moving. That makes them sticky and high-value \\u2014 especially when they replace multiple tools. Businesses rely on these platforms to grow. They drive leads, automate follow-ups, and keep deals moving. That makes them sticky and high-value \\u2014 especially when they", "score": 0.3525366, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://skrapp.io/sales-glossary/average-revenue-per-user-arpu", "title": "Average Revenue Per User (ARPU)", "content": "sales income your business generates within the chosen timeframe (month, quarter, year). + Number of Users: This refers to the total number of customers you have during that same timeframe. Imagine a company generates $10,000 in revenue in a month and has 100 users. ARPU = $10,000 / 100 users = $100 per user This indicates that the company earns an average of $100 from each user in that particular month.  + ARPU is typically calculated on a monthly basis, but you can adjust the time frame", "score": 0.33482918, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://kinde.com/learn/billing/metrics/average-revenue-per-user-arpu", "title": "Kinde Average Revenue Per User (ARPU)", "content": "Suppose last month you made $100,000 from 10 active customers, you\\u2019d have an ARPU of $10,000. When it gets really interesting is when you compare the metric over different periods. If last year this month you had 5 customers and $60,000 in revenue, then your ARPU has fallen and you might need to assess the customers you\\u2019re acquiring and value you\\u2019re providing.\\n\\n## Things to consider when calculating ARPU", "score": 0.27204314, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.fluentco.com/glossary/term/average-revenue-per-user", "title": "Average Revenue per User (ARPU) | Fluent", "content": "ARPU considers all these revenue streams and calculates the average amount each active user spends during the chosen timeframe.\\n\\nHow to measure average revenue per user:\\n\\nThe formula for ARPU is:\\n\\nARPU = Total Revenue / Number of Active Users (in a specific timeframe)\\n\\nFor example, if a social media platform generates $1 million in revenue during a month and has 100,000 active users, their ARPU for that month would be $10 (\\u2063\\u2063$1,000,000 / 100,000).", "score": 0.25992236, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://fluentco.com/glossary/term/average-revenue-per-user", "title": "Average Revenue per User (ARPU) | Fluent", "content": "# Average Revenue per User (ARPU). What is average revenue per user?. Average revenue per user or ARPU is a key metric used in mobile app marketing. It specifically measures the average amount of revenue generated by an active user of a mobile app over a defined period (month, quarter, year). How does average revenue per user work?. Mobile apps can generate revenue through various models, including:.  In-app purchases: Users pay real money for virtual goods, subscriptions, or premium features", "score": 0.23199724, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.airbridge.io/ko/glossary/average-revenue-per-user-arpu", "title": "Average revenue per user (ARPU) - Airbridge", "content": "What this indicates is that the business generated an average of $10 in revenue per customer over the month. ARPU, on the other hand, measures the revenue generated by a business per user or customer over a specific time frame, typically a month or a quarter. Also, ARPU can be calculated by dividing the total revenue by the number of users or customers. One of the key benefits of tracking ARPU is that it allows marketers to identify trends in customer spending. For example, if 